-- Liberia Inflation Accelerates to 4.7% in July From 2.5%, Central Bank Says
-- B y   A n s u   K o n n e h
-- 2010-09-24T15:32:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/liberia-inflation-accelerates-to-4-7-in-july-from-2-5-central-bank-says.html
Inflation in Liberia accelerated to
4.7 percent in July, from 2.5 percent in June, the Central Bank
of Liberia said today.  The June rate fell from 8 percent recorded in May, the
Monrovia-based bank said in its monthly economic bulletin handed
to reporters in the capital today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ansu Konneh in Monrovia at 
 akonneh@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
